<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ880121-0137 </DOCNO><HL> Molecular Genetics Inc. </HL><SO> </SO><CO> MOGN </CO><DATELINE> MINNETONKA, Minn.  </DATELINE><TEXT>   Molecular Genetics Inc. said its board adopted an anti-takeover measure involving the distribution of common stock-purchase rights to shareholders.    Under certain circumstances, the rights allow holders to buy stock in Molecular Genetics, or the acquiring company, at half price.    Molecular Genetics, a biotechnology concern, said the rights will be distributed on Feb. 2 and will expire 10 years later. The company added that the move wasn't in response to any known efforts to acquire it. </TEXT></DOC>